caption: Enjoyed an evening out with friends at this great restaurant. Staff was friendly, service was great, food... delicious! They have a wide selection of unique and tasty tacos. I'll be back when I'm in the city. Definitely recommend this to you if you're in the Lakeview area of Chicago.

So new craft taco place- they have another in Portage Park. Nice to have something unique and delicious here.   They are one of the only places that carries Birria tacos- they call it the Tijuana.  Homemade tortillas. Comes with a dipping sauce -wow. I would eat anything dipped in that sauce. Damn. Delicious.  Also had a Chile relleno taco- oh god so good.  Coming back tomorrow- have to try everything now.

Wow- another hit for Tatas Tacos!  I'm a fan of the Six Corners location and love the creative tacos, hand trimmed steak house quality meats, salads, fresh juice cocktails, craft beers, fresh guacamole-  I could go on and on!  Summers on the patio are going to be AMAZING!!! My favorite Taco- hard to choose just one but the jibarito and sirena ...and the poke- are a must try!!!  ....and the burritos too!!! lol hard to choose

Do yourself a favor and visit this new local taco spot. Fast and friendly service, and delicious tacos. We did takeout for our first visit and look forward to enjoying the patio when temps warm up (or dining in once things open back up!). I’d strongly suggest the mole and camaron classic tacos. Enjoy!

So delicious! I think this location is only open for grub hub or seamless right now but can’t wait for them to open dine-in.  I’ve had the tacos from the original spot in Portage park and am so glad there’s one in Lakeview now! Did not disappoint. The camarón and Frida are my favorite so far, but we got al pastor and Tata’s too and they were both incredible too! Can’t wait to try the others. Also it was fast, our order arrived only 25 minutes after we placed it :)
